# Stephen Salerno

I am a post-doctoral research fellow in the [Fred Hutch Data Science Lab](https://hutchdatascience.org/). My research centers on statistical methods for multivariate data and machine learning for high dimensional survival analysis, as well as its applications to clinical quality measure development, public reporting efforts, and health policy surrounding kidney diseases and lung cancer. I am also passionate about applying my skill set to public service and am active in data for good initiatives at the University of Michigan and beyond.

**Education:** <br> PhD \| Biostatistics \| University of Michigan \| 2023 <br> MS \| Biostatistics \| University of Michigan \| 2018 <br> BS \| Biometry & Statistics \| Cornell University \| 2016 <br>

**Experience:** <br> Post-Doctoral Research Fellow \| Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center \| Seattle, WA

